  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Essential Healthcare Service Delivery, Port Loko District, Sierra Leone</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rehabilitation of Existing PHU Structures: Structural repairs on the existing structures i.e.
ceiling/roof works, plastering walls, drainages and reinforcements, to ensure that they meet the
acceptable MOHS standards Water, 
Sanitation and Hygiene: Construction/rehabilitation of water wells, repairing toilets,
provision of sanitary means of waste disposal
installation of Solar and the Provision of Delivery Beds: Installation of solar power in each PHU to
provide lighting so that delivery can be done at night and provision of delivery beds.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will strengthen health service systems and improve health outcomes across two
chiefdoms in Port Loko district. It will target 4 PHUs which direct benefit 25,000 people (35% male,
45% female and 20% children).</narrative>
  </description>
